HEADWORD: Precursory
<hw>Pre*cur"so*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praecursorius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Preceding as a precursor or
harbinger; indicating something to follow; <as>as, <ex>precursory</ex>
symptoms of a fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precursory</ent>⟦br⟧

